f   Papp  , meaning ‘priest (of the Catholic or Orthodox Church)’. This surname is also found in Romania, Slovakia, Croatia, and Serbia, and also among Rusyns (in Serbia and Croatia). See also   Pop   2 and   Popa  .","English: variant of   Pape   1."],"variants":[{"name":"Papp","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Hungarian Laszlo, Zoltan, Geza, Istvan, Gabor, Miklos, Tibor, Arpad, Denes, Imre, Attila.","German (Bavaria, Tyrol): from Middle High German <i>pap</i> ‘baby food’, Dutch <i>pap</i> ‘porridge, pap’, hence perhaps a nickname denoting someone who had lost his teeth or subsisted on a meager diet.","Hungarian: from <i>pap</i> ‘priest (of the Catholic or Orthodox Church)’, probably an occupational name for someone in the service of a priest or a nickname for a pious person. This surname is also found in Romania and Slovakia, and also among Rusyns. Compare   Pap   and   Pop  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Earl Gwerystan ap Gwynnan Brochwell of Powys of Devonshire was born about 0890, in Rhuddlan, Flintshire, Wales, his father, Gwynnog Farfsych ap Lles, was 22 and his mother, Fynwyla ferch Iorwerth, was 17. He married Morfydd Ferch Owain of Wales in 0924, in Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 0960, in Powys, Wales, United Kingdom, at the age of 71."},"et":{"about 0890–960":"umbes 0890–0960","0890–0960":"0890–0960","0903–1019":"0903–1019","0904–Female":"0904–Surnud","0920–1008":"0920–1008","0934–0963":"0934–0963","0870–Male":"0870–Surnud","0875–Female":"0875–Surnud","before 890":"enne 0890","0890":"0890","0875":"0875","0963":"0963","1008":"1008","1019":"1019","0920":"0920","960":"0960","0960":"0960","0870":"0870","934":"0934","0903":"0903","924":"0924","0904":"0904","0934":"0934","about 0890":"umbes 0890","Powys, Cymru":"Powys, Wales, United Kingdom","Cwybr, Rhuddlan, Flintshire, Wales":"Rhuddlan, Flintshire, Wales","Devon, England":"Devon, England","Montgomeryshire, Wales":"Montgomeryshire, Wales